verses.roman:
tabe aṣṭa-kauḍira khājā kare samarpaṇa
svarūpa-ājñāya govinda tāhā kare samādhāna

synonyms: tabe—then; aṣṭa-kauḍira—costing eight kauḍis; khājā—the sweetmeat named khājā; kare samarpaṇa—offers; svarūpa-ājñāya—by the order of Svarūpa Dāmodara; govinda—the personal servant of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; tāhā—that; kare samādhāna—arranges.
translation: Raghunātha dāsa then began offering the costly sweetmeats known as khājā, which Govinda, following the order of Svarūpa Dāmodara, would supply.
